# Hook Architecture and Reusability

- Use actions and filters to integrate behavior instead of tight coupling.
- Keep callback functions single-purpose and testable.
- Prefix custom hooks, option keys, meta keys, and constants with project namespace.
- Reuse shared utilities for repeated formatting, validation, or query logic.
- Keep admin, frontend, and data-access concerns separated.
- Prefer composition through small modules over inheritance-heavy classes.
- Ensure every public extension point has predictable arguments and defaults.
- When deprecating behavior, keep compatibility shims and clear migration notes.
